x — a personal CLI for reading X (Twitter) free public surfaces.

This program derives from Nitter (https://github.com/zedeus/nitter), in
particular its approach to X's web-client GraphQL API: the hardcoded public
web bearer token, the versioned GraphQL operation/query-id map, the
guest-token activation flow, the variables/features request shape, cursor
pagination, and the shared "legacy" tweet/user JSON model. Those techniques
were studied from Nitter's source and reimplemented here in Go.

